cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC. 

The paper discusses existential rules, which are a type of data dependency commonly used in databases. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of existential rules in Ontology-based Query Answering, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also introduces a novel semantic definition for OCQA ontologies, which is related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also uses mathematical proofs and establishes the expressive completeness of certain classes of dependencies, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
